CKNOWLEDGMENTS
We would like to thank the Anne Ray Foundation for fund-
ing this project. We would like to acknowledge two anonymous
reviewers for helping to improve this manuscript. We would like
to thank Mark Nigrelli and the U.S. Forest Service for gener-
ously providing unpublished data related to 4FRI and this pro-
ject. We would like to thank Stephen Horner for providing
estimates of the wood products coming from harvest materials
in the region. We would like to acknowledge Rob Scheller, Will
Flatley, and Matt Hurteau for technical expertise and advice on
the LANDIS-II models. We would like to thank the New Mex-
ico Chapter of TNC, specifically Laura McCarthy, Anne Brad-
ley, and Steven Bassett, for initial discussions on forest carbon
work in the southwest. The data set used for future climate
data, MACAv2-METDATA, was produced with funding from
the Regional Approaches to Climate Change (REACCH) pro-
ject and the Southeast Climate Adaptation Science Center
(SECASC). We acknowledge the World Climate Research Pro-
gramme
s Working Group on Coupled Modeling, which is
responsible for CMIP, and we thank the climate modeling
groups for producing and making available their model output.
For CMIP, the U.S. Department of Energy
s Program for Cli-
mate Model Diagnosis and Intercomparison provides coordi-
nating support and led development of software infrastructure
in partnership with the Global Organization for Earth System
Science Portals.
